      "created_at": "2021-05-29T07:18:44.363Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Build up slowly.  If only 60 minutes is comfortable now that is good.  I know a top coach that is a biomechanics expert and he does not recommend more than 90 minutes on an indoor trainer.  The dynamic movements of outdoors are healthier.  Many people do long indoor sessions without obvious problems but I am just passing on this wisdom.  That said sure, you can take breaks, it\u2019s not a problem.  Outdoors we get lots of breaks.  Stop lights, traffic\u2026 or just a sight seeing break. <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"></p>",
